aditional natural history museums. Through a unique historical dataset of over 1,000 internal documents from creationist organizations and an analysis of media coverage, Creating the Creation Museum shows how the museum works as a site of social movement activity and a place to contest the secular mainstream. Oberlin ultimately argues that the Creation Museum has real-world consequences in today’s polarized era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aCreationismzUnited States. 0aMuseumsxSocial aspectszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology of Religion.2bisacsh  aAnswers in Genesis.  aCreation Science Museum.  aCreation Science Politics.  aCreation Science.  aOld Earth Creationism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z97831107227030 cprintz978147988164240uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479881642.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479897520423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479897520/original  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-072270-3  New York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-al